<number id="3DAB248D863D8676FC886D2CFC47FACA" box="[857,917,1312,1338]" pageId="4" pageNumber="23" value="1861.0">1861</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13582A2F863D8676FC7C6D2CFC2DFACA" box="[941,1023,1312,1338]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1847,1871]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1787]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,194,1789]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Lygephila sp., adults. 1, L. stueningi, male, holotype, China; 2, 3, ditto, female, paratype; China; 4, ditto, male paratype, China; 5, 6, L. ludicra, Russia, Tuva, female and male; 7, L. longicoecum, male, holotype, China; 8, L. maxima, male, Russia, Khabarovsk." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/184113/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">
Figs. 
<number id="3DAB248D863D8676FC3E6D2CFC2DFACA" box="[1007,1023,1312,1338]" pageId="4" pageNumber="23" value="8.16">8</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13582A2F863D8676FBDC6D2CFBFFFACA" box="[1037,1069,1312,1338]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 16" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1948,1972]" captionTargetBox="[159,1415,355,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[159,1424,355,1924]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 16. Lygephila sp., male genitalia. 13, L. stueningi, male, paratype, genit. prep. 5882 M. Fibiger; 14, L. ludicra, Turkey, genit. prep. 3561 M. Fibiger; 15, L. longicoecum, holotype, China, ZFMK genit. prep. 2019 V. Kononenko; 16, L. maxima, South Korea, CIS genit. prep. 169 - 1 Han H. L." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/184115/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">16</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13582A2F863D8676FBE86D2CFB8BFACA" box="[1081,1113,1312,1338]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 20" captionStartId="6.[151,269,961,985]" captionTargetBox="[199,1404,156,900]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[185,1405,156,915]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 20. Lygephila sp., female genitalia. 17, L. stueningi, paratype, genit. prep. 5883 M. Fibiger; 18, L. ludicra, Mongolia, genit. prep. C 21 B. Goater; 19, L. maxima, Russian Far East, Primorye Territory, genit. prep. 5725 M. Fibiger; 20, L. longicoecum, paratype, China, IBSS genit. prep. 698 V. Kononenko." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/184116/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">
<number id="3DAB248D863D8676FBE86D2CFB8BFACA" box="[1081,1113,1312,1338]" pageId="4" pageNumber="23" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D29863D8676FBBE6D2DFAF6FACA" box="[1135,1316,1313,1338]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lygephila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longicoecum">
<emphasis id="B917EAB8863D8676FBBE6D2DFAF6FACA" box="[1135,1316,1313,1338]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">L. longicoecum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs by the straight medial shade from reniform stigma to ventral margin of forewing, and by the unicolorous light brown hindwing. In the male genitalia it differs by the narrower uncus, the shorter tegumen, the broader vinculum and saccus, the waved costa of valva, the huge clasper-ampulla complex, the extremely long sacculus, and the extremely long, narrow coecum of aedeagus. The female genitalia differ by the broad and irregular cone-shaped, heavily sclerotised antrum which is subapically expanded, and the globular corpus bursae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3796521863D8676FF146E1CFB7BF8EA" pageId="4" pageNumber="23" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BDC36AA863D8676FF146E1CFB7BF8EA" blockId="4.[151,1437,912,1938]" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="B917EAB8863D8676FF146E1CFE8FF9DA" bold="true" box="[197,349,1552,1578]" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">Description.</emphasis>
Imago (
<figureCitation id="13582A2F863D8676FE1B6E1CFDC5F9DA" box="[458,535,1552,1578]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1847,1871]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1787]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,194,1789]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Lygephila sp., adults. 1, L. stueningi, male, holotype, China; 2, 3, ditto, female, paratype; China; 4, ditto, male paratype, China; 5, 6, L. ludicra, Russia, Tuva, female and male; 7, L. longicoecum, male, holotype, China; 8, L. maxima, male, Russia, Khabarovsk." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/184113/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<number id="3DAB248D863D8676FDD76E1CFDC5F9DA" box="[518,535,1552,1578]" pageId="4" pageNumber="23" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Wingspan: 
<quantity id="4C9B9B4F863D8676FD6D6E1CFC91F9DA" box="[700,835,1552,1578]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.2" metricValueMax="5.4" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="23" unit="mm" value="52.0" valueMax="54.0" valueMin="50.0">50–54 mm</quantity>
. Head with long brown scales; coal-black scales between antennae and above on head and patagia; thorax and ground colour of forewing grey, suffused with brown scales, including fringes; all cross-lines present, well marked; postmedial area by costa blackish brown; terminal line marked by small, black intervenal dots; medial shade sharply angled by reniform stigma, from angle straight towards both margins; reniform stigma dark brown, with four black spots; orbicular stigma absent. Hindwing light brown, without pattern. Underside of forewing unicolorous brown; hindwing light brown. 
<emphasis id="B917EAB8863D8676FEFC6F0CFDA2F8EA" bold="true" box="[301,624,1792,1818]" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">Male and female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13582A2F863D8676FD516F0CFD31F8EA" box="[640,739,1792,1818]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 16" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1948,1972]" captionTargetBox="[159,1415,355,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[159,1424,355,1924]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 16. Lygephila sp., male genitalia. 13, L. stueningi, male, paratype, genit. prep. 5882 M. Fibiger; 14, L. ludicra, Turkey, genit. prep. 3561 M. Fibiger; 15, L. longicoecum, holotype, China, ZFMK genit. prep. 2019 V. Kononenko; 16, L. maxima, South Korea, CIS genit. prep. 169 - 1 Han H. L." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/184115/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">
Figs. 
<number id="3DAB248D863D8676FD126F0CFD31F8EA" box="[707,739,1792,1818]" pageId="4" pageNumber="23" value="15.2">15</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13582A2F863D8676FD3E6F0CFCDCF8EA" box="[751,782,1792,1818]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 20" captionStartId="6.[151,269,961,985]" captionTargetBox="[199,1404,156,900]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[185,1405,156,915]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 20. Lygephila sp., female genitalia. 17, L. stueningi, paratype, genit. prep. 5883 M. Fibiger; 18, L. ludicra, Mongolia, genit. prep. C 21 B. Goater; 19, L. maxima, Russian Far East, Primorye Territory, genit. prep. 5725 M. Fibiger; 20, L. longicoecum, paratype, China, IBSS genit. prep. 698 V. Kononenko." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/184116/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">20</figureCitation>
) are as described for the subgenus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3796521863D8676FF146F24FADDF89A" pageId="4" pageNumber="23" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BDC36AA863D8676FF146F24FADDF89A" blockId="4.[151,1437,912,1938]" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="B917EAB8863D8676FF146F24FE8CF8B2" bold="true" box="[197,350,1832,1858]" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">Distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13582A2F863D8676FEA36F24FE1FF8B2" box="[370,461,1832,1858]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="8.[151,255,1819,1843]" captionTargetBox="[369,1217,1259,1771]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[367,1223,1257,1781]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 25. Distribution map of L. stueningi, L. longicoecum, and Apopestes curiosa." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/184118/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<number id="3DAB248D863D8676FE7D6F24FE1FF8B2" box="[428,461,1832,1858]" pageId="4" pageNumber="23" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
). The species is only known from its 
<typeStatus id="54D88808863D8676FC4F6F24FC02F8B2" box="[926,976,1832,1858]" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">type</typeStatus>
locality, south west 
<collectingCountry id="F374763A863D8676FB1C6F24FAC4F8B2" box="[1229,1302,1832,1858]" name="China" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">China</collectingCountry>
, Tapaishan Range, Province Shansi. The moths were collected at light in the mountains from 
<quantity id="4C9B9B4F863D8676FB876F5CFAD9F89A" box="[1110,1291,1872,1898]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="1.7" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="4" pageNumber="23" unit="m" value="1500.0" valueMax="1700.0" valueMin="1300.0">
<date id="FFDD106A863D8676FB876F5CFB38F89A" box="[1110,1258,1872,1898]" pageId="4" pageNumber="23" value="1300" valueMax="1700">1300 to1700</date>
m
</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3796521863D8676FF146F74FB4EF862" box="[197,1180,1912,1938]" pageId="4" pageNumber="23" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BDC36AA863D8676FF146F74FB4EF862" blockId="4.[151,1437,912,1938]" box="[197,1180,1912,1938]" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="B917EAB8863D8676FF146F74FE80F862" bold="true" box="[197,338,1912,1938]" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named after the conspicuously long and narrow coecum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
